Material used.Material Source: Cell line (Neuro - 2a) and Primary - cultured hippocampal neurons
Material used.Material Name: Neuro - 2a cells, Hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18 C57BL/6J mice
Material used.Description: Neuro - 2a cells were maintained in Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum, 100 units/ml penicillin and 100 mg/ml streptomycin. Hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 C57BL/6J mice as described. Tissue fragments of the hippocampal areas were added to Hank's Balanced Salt Solution containing 0.25% trypsin and 0.1 mg/ml DNase I, incubated, dissociated, and resuspended in Neurobasal - A medium supplemented with 2% B - 27 supplement, 2 mM glutamine, 100 units/ml penicillin and 100 mg/ml streptomycin. Dissociated cells were plated onto polyethyleneimine - coated 35 - mm dishes.

Experiment Method.Readout type: Qualitative (immunoblotting to detect presence/absence of proteins)

Readout description.Variant: N.D. (HGVS nomenclature not provided in literature, requires API call for standardization, e.g., UCH - L1:D30K)
Readout description.Conclusion: The secretion level of D30K UCH - L1 was significantly lower than that of wild - type UCH - L1
Readout description.Result Description: FLAG - tagged D30K UCH - L1 was transiently expressed in Neuro - 2a cells. The secreted level of D30K UCH - L1 was significantly lower than that of wild - type UCH - L1 as detected by immunoblotting.

Biological replicates.Description: The data are expressed as mean ± SD (n = 3) in multiple experiments indicating biological replicates were performed.

Statistical analysis method.Statistical analysis method: The Student's t - test was used for comparison of two groups. Dunnett's multiple comparison test was used for comparison of more than two groups.
